## Step 5: Summary

📋 **Test List Created:**

**Feature:** MHPCO Claim Office Premium Quoting and Claims Processing

**Test File:** src/claim-office.spec.ts

**Base Functionality Tests:** 18 test cases (11 quote tests + 7 claims tests)

**Test Cases** (ordered simple → complex):

### Premium Quoting (Simple → Complex)
1. ✅ Should calculate base premium for a single sword
2. ✅ Should calculate base premium for a single component
3. ✅ Should apply special premium for 3 alike components
4. ✅ Should apply 50% surcharge for cursed items
5. ✅ Should apply 30% surcharge for highly enchanted items (level >= 5)
6. ✅ Should apply 10% initial assessment surcharge for new customers (0 years)
7. ✅ Should apply 15% discount on contracts after the first
8. ✅ Should apply 20% loyalty discount for long-standing customers (>= 2 years)
9. ✅ Should add 5G processing fee to every premium
10. ✅ Should round all amounts to whole G in MHPCO's favor (round up)
11. ✅ Should calculate premium for multiple mixed items in one quote

### Claims Processing (Simple → Complex)
12. ✅ Should calculate payout for a single damage claim
13. ✅ Should apply 100G deductible per damage event
14. ✅ Should reimburse 50% for damage to highly enchanted items (level >= 8)
15. ✅ Should fully reimburse damage to dragon material items
16. ✅ Should cap total payout at twice the insurance sum
17. ✅ Should track remaining cap across multiple claims on the same policy
18. ✅ Should return zero payout when deductible exceeds damage amount

**Advanced Features** (NOT included - save for later):
- Specific material-based premiums (other than dragon)
- Complex multi-item interactions
- Full error handling and validation
- CLI integration and JSON parsing
